"{\"uid\": \"thetab.com-2024-07-31-erm-okay-so-what-on-earth-actually-are-the-paris-2024-olympics-mascots-the-phryges\", \"text\": \"Genuinely thought they were supposed to be a poor imitation of the Eiffel Tower  If you have watched any of the Paris 2024 Olympics, whether through TikToks, memes or *gasp* the actual TV, you will have almost certainly seen the slightly terrifying mascots, the Phryges. There is already something slightly eerie about mascots in general, but what exactly are the mascots supposed to be?  At first glance they look like a combination of a weird poo, crumpled Eiffel Tower and as one fan elegantly put it, \\\"a clitoris.\\\" But it's safe to say there is definitely nothing sexual about the Paris 2024 mascots, who play a key role during the Olympics and are actually called the Phryges.  Reminded of the 2024 Olympic mascots and audibly groaned. \\ud83d\\ude29pic.twitter.com/B7t94gRrRz  - Busiris (@Busiris)April 2, 2024  The Phryges are actually based on the famous Phrygian cap, a symbol of freedom in France. The cap has been worn throughout major events in French history, most notably during the revolution where the cap became a symbol of a free republic. The French National Archives show records of Phrygian caps worn during the construction of Paris' Notre-Dame cathedral in 1163, during the Revolution of 1789, during work to build the Eiffel Tower, and during the Paris 1924 Olympic Games.  There are two different Phryges, one for the Olympics and another for the Paralympics who has a running prosthetic. They are both girlies, obviously, and even have their own personalities. The Olympic Phryge is described as \\\"thoughtful and an astute strategist\\\" who \\\"is modest and prefers to hide her emotions.\\\" What a mood.  France's ambassador to the UK has had a meeting - documented by official photos - with the Olympic mascots and there is not one thing about this I do not lovepic.twitter.com/0S9H8xY6c5  - Tom Hourigan (@TomHourigan)July 30, 2024  As for the Paralympic mascot, she \\\"hates being bored and loves to try new things.\\\" The Paris 2024 president Tony Estanguet explained why they chose the caps to be their mascots, saying: \\\"We chose an ideal rather than an animal. We chose the Phrygian cap because it's a very strong symbol for the French Republic. For French people, it's a very well-known object that is a symbol of freedom, an object that will represent mascots all across the world. The fact that the Paralympics mascot has a visible disability also sends a strong message: to promote inclusion.\\\"  \\u2022Inside Olympian Adam Peaty's relationships with Holly Ramsay and ex-girlfriend Eiri Munro  \\u2022Simone Biles net worth: The insane amount she's worth from her gymnastics success  \\u2022Grab your glasses and laugh at the best memes about Steve the nerdy pommel horse hero  Featured images via YouTube.  Scan the mo to help a bro  Christmas is all about lists, and trust me, this one's the only one you will need to escape the crowds and keep within your student budget  I honestly did not expect that  I am a bit lost  He does not hold back  'Join us as we reclaim our streets, our nights and our rights'  They hit so hard after the second film  'It is a great honour to present Emma with an Honorary Doctorate, and we look forward to continuing our work together in the future.'  The power is all in your hands now  The theories are insane  Time to see how long you spent binging your fave shows  Christmas is all about lists, and trust me, this one's the only one you will need to escape the crowds and keep within your student budget  I honestly did not expect that  I am a bit lost  He does not hold back  'Join us as we reclaim our streets, our nights and our rights'  They hit so hard after the second film  'It is a great honour to present Emma with an Honorary Doctorate, and we look forward to continuing our work together in the future.'  The power is all in your hands now  The theories are insane